      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we use setjmp and longjmp, we really just go back to where we were on the stack.  The destructors for objects in scope are not called.  This means, e.g. ~vector() is not called on these vectors, and they\u0027ll never free their memory.  Are we okay with leaking memory, leaving mutexes permanently locked, etc?\n\nIf not I think we should look at using exceptions instead.  They\u0027ll act a lot like setjmp (try-catch) and longjmp (throw), but will call destructors as they unwind the stack back up to the catch.",
